# Feature: MatchOnce attribute on observables (Species-type, multi-embedding)
# Tests: when a species matches the observable pattern in multiple ways
#   (pattern has degeneracy across homotypic sites), a Species-type
#   observable with matchOnce="1" counts the species ONCE regardless of
#   embedding multiplicity.  Silent-ignore of matchOnce would collapse
#   the Species count to the Molecules (embedding) count.
# Tier: base
#
# BNG2 2.9.3 NOTE: BNG2 auto-sets matchOnce="1" on every Species-type
# observable pattern and does NOT propagate user-written `{MatchOnce}`
# on Molecules-type observables to XML (RuleWorld/bionetgen#312).  The
# Species-type multi-embedding case is therefore the only testable
# form of MatchOnce through our toolchain; this model covers it.
#
# Expected at saturation:
#   - A has two homotypic b-sites; at equilibrium all 50 A's have both
#     bonds (kf*B_tot >> kr).
#   - Molecules  A(b!+): 2 embeddings × 50 mols = 100
#   - Species    A(b!+): 1 match per species × 50 population = 50
# Verdict relies on RM-vs-NFsim z-score: if RM silently ignored
# matchOnce="1", A_species_any would track A_mol_embeds (→100) and
# NFsim would disagree.

begin model
begin parameters
    A_tot  50
    B_tot  200
    kf     10.0   # fast binding — drives A to doubly-bound state
    kr     0.01   # slow unbinding
end parameters

begin molecule types
    A(b,b)
    B(a)
end molecule types

begin seed species
    A(b,b)  A_tot
    B(a)    B_tot
end seed species

begin observables
    Molecules  A_mol_embeds   A(b!+)    # counts bound-site embeddings
    Species    A_species_any  A(b!+)    # auto-matchOnce="1" in XML
end observables

begin reaction rules
    A(b) + B(a) <-> A(b!1).B(a!1)  kf, kr
end reaction rules
end model

begin actions
simulate({method=>"nf",t_end=>10,n_steps=>50})
end actions
